 "text": "\n\nFix: \n\n\u003cvuxml xmlns=\"http://www.vuxml.org/apps/vuxml-1\"\u003e\n   \u003cvuln vid=\"130b85c8-6568-4a6d-940d-11acbe607fa6\"\u003e\n     \u003ctopic\u003emoinmoin -- MoinMoin AttachFile.py Cross-Site Scripting\u003c/topic\u003e\n     \u003caffects\u003e\n       \u003cpackage\u003e\n         \u003cname\u003emoinmoin\u003c/name\u003e\n         \u003crange\u003e\u003clt\u003e1.8.1\u003c/lt\u003e\u003c/range\u003e\n       \u003c/package\u003e\n     \u003c/affects\u003e\n     \u003cdescription\u003e\n       \u003cbody xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"\u003e\n         \u003cp\u003eSANS reports:\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003cblockquote cite=\"http://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/500197\"\u003e\n           \u003cp\u003eThe application is exposed to cross-site scripting attacks because it\nfails to sufficiently sanitize user-supplied input to the rename\nparameter in the action/AttachFile.py source file. MoinMoin versions\nprior to 1.8.1 are vulnerable.\u003c/p\u003e\n         \u003c/blockquote\u003e\n       \u003c/body\u003e\n     \u003c/description\u003e\n     \u003creferences\u003e\n      \u003curl\u003ehttp://www.securityfocus.com/archive/1/500197\u003c/url\u003e\n     \u003c/references\u003e\n     \u003cdates\u003e\n       \u003cdiscovery\u003e2009-01-08\u003c/discovery\u003e\n       \u003centry\u003e2009-01-23\u003c/entry\u003e\n     \u003c/dates\u003e\n   \u003c/vuln\u003e"
